We took full advantage of this early summer like weather and the kid’s PD day this past week. Core memories made at Seba Beach! 👌🏻 It was only an hour drive from Edmonton. Felt so good to slow down for a day and just enjoy each other’s presence. I had tons of question about the rental, it’s the @littlelakehouseca. Summer dates opened today if you’re looking to snag a stay before they are gone! We easily fit as a family of four with smaller kids. There’s a pull out couch in the living room and one bedroom. 
For transparency we were hosted but paid Airbnb’s fees. My thoughts and opinions are my own. We loved our stay and the Reno of this little cabin was amazing. I see why they are super hosts, it was stocked. Highly recommend. We are currently looking at their other lake house with the additional bedroom, that’s how much we loved it. 
What are your summer plans?

Hey 👋🏻 Edmonton and surrounding area, do you know @pep.society? Take the first step into health and recovery as a family. PEP supports and educates families and caregivers dealing with the effects of substance use and addiction in loved ones. Check pepsociety.ca for an up-to-date schedule of professionally-facilitated and innovative
programming, and you can call their toll-free family support line at 1-877-991-2737. You can untie the knots of addiction and start the journey
of family recovery today.

It’s time to declutter for a cause! Join Diabetes Canada this Saturday from 9am to 1pm for their clothing drive in! For my #YEG peeps: 
1155 Windermere street Way SW in the Superstore parking lot. 
It’s so easy, just fill your trunk with bags of gently used clothing and small household items. When you arrive at the event pop your trunk and volunteers will collect your donations! Just like that, you’ll be diverting textiles from landfills, helping fund research and sending kids with type 1 diabetes to camp. For more info visit declutter.diabetes.ca 
 #diabetespartner #dcdeclutter

All and all this was a very successful trip. Our last Disneyland trip was April 22’ and we were lucky enough to visited World in October 22’.
